SIMPLE: indisposition
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indisposition
<hw>In*dis`po*si"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>indisposition</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being indisposed; disinclination;
<as>as, the <ex>indisposition</ex> of two substances to
combine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A general <qex>indisposition</qex> towards believing.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slight disorder or illness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rather as an <qex>indisposition</qex> in health than as any set
sickness.</q> <rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indisputability</ent>⟦br⟧
